# Barkdown
Barkdown is a stupid little markup language made using regex rules in Python 
## Demo
Demo is hosted at link:https://barkdown.4lvaret.tech
## Running from source
1. Install Python (figure out how to do that for your os) <br>
2. Using git, clone link:https://github.com/simpansoftware/Barkdown <br>
3. Run `pip install flask` <br>
4. Run `python main.py`, this will return some stuff about it being a dev server, but go to localhost:2048 and you should see the Barkdown renderer.
## What is the valid syntax?
See this and test.bd as examples, and look in syntax.bd or link:https://barkdown.4lvaret.tech/usage for rules or
